# Project authority (holy grail)

`docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md` is the **authoritative** “how to build” standard. Pair it with `docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md` (architecture) and `docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md` (what to ship and when).

**Precedence:** If a user prompt conflicts with these guidelines, **follow PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md** unless the user explicitly updates that document.

## Required references

- **`PROJECT_PLAN.md`** — stack, services, Socket.IO + RabbitMQ, repo layout.
- **`PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md`** — TypeScript, Node, MongoDB, APIs, React/Redux, tests, process.
- **`TASK_CHECKLIST.md`** — tasks/subtasks; capture work there before large features; check off as you ship.

## Process (non-negotiable)

- **Deprecated APIs:** do not add or perpetuate deprecated Node, browser/DOM, React, or library APIs—use current documented replacements (`PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md` §1.1).
- Do **not** implement beyond the request; no speculative features.
- Prefer **incremental** changes; preserve existing behaviour unless replacing by design.
- **OpenAPI:** any new or changed REST route **updates the OpenAPI spec in the same PR**; Swagger UI on **messaging-service** stays accurate.
- **TASK_CHECKLIST.md:** update it when feature-level work is part of the plan.

## Before merge (quick gate)

Strict TS; env validated at startup; no secrets in repo; authz on mutating routes; MongoDB access patterns reasoned; list APIs paginated with server-enforced limits; OpenAPI in sync; ESLint clean; UI tests-first for new/changed components when touching `web-client`; Redux/hooks per guidelines for global client state.
